 }

Q10 WAP to take date as an input in below given format and convert the date format and 
display the result as given below.
User Input date format – “DD/MM/YYYY” (27/11/2022)
Output format –
“Day – DD , Month – MM , Year – YYYY” (Day – 27 ,Month – 07 , Year – 2022)
Answer: #include<stdio.h>
int main()
 {
    int day,month,year;
 printf("Enter day in DD/MM/YYYY format\n");
 scanf("%d/%d/%d",&day,&month,&year);

 printf("%d day %d month and %d year",day,month,year);
 return 0;
 }

Q11 WAP to take time as an input in below given format and convert the time format and 
display the result as given below.
User Input date format – “HH:MM”
Output format – “HH hour and MM Minute”
Example –
“11:25” converted to “11 Hour and 25 Minute”
Answer:    #include<stdio.h>
                 int main()
 {
    int hour,min;
printf(“Enter time in HH:MM format\n”);
 scanf("%d:%d",&hour,&min);

 printf("%d Hours and %d minutes",hour,min);
 return 0;
 }

